### Fastify Async/Await Route Handler

Source: https://fastify.dev/docs/v3.29.x/Reference/Routes

Utilize async/await in route handlers. Returning a value from the handler automatically sends it as the response body. `reply.send()` can also be explicitly called.

```javascript
fastify.get('/', options, async function (request, reply) {

  var data = await getData()

  var processed = await processData(data)

  return processed

})
```

